  "text": "In recent years, the pcrformance of many object detection applications has received a boost by the \"Viola-Jones\" detector [I 11, an approach that discriminates object from non-object image iatches with help of machine learning techniques. Its main idea is to generate an over-complete set of (up to 100000) efficiently computable Haar wavelet features, combine them with simple threshold classifiers, and utilize AdaBoost [CITATION_1] to select and weight the most discriminative subset of waveIet features and threshold classifiers. Supported by an efficient wavelet feature computation with help of the so-called inregrul i m g e and a cascaded classifier setup, those systems were shown to be able to solve many practical problems in realtime 112, 141.",
